
Custom Programming Language - Keywords

This document provides an overview of the keywords and their usage in the custom Hindi-based programming language. Each keyword is designed to make programming fun and intuitive!

---

Keywords

1. dekho
- Purpose: Print text or values to the console.
- Usage:
  dekho("Namaste Duniya!");
  dekho(42);

---

2. naya
- Purpose: Declare a new variable.
- Usage:
  naya x = 10;
  naya y = "Shabd";

---

3. kaam
- Purpose: Define a new function.
- Usage:
  kaam add(purna x, purna y) {
      wapas x + y;
  }

---

4. agar
- Purpose: Define an `if` condition.
- Usage:
  agar (x > 10) {
      dekho("Badi sankhya!");
  }

---

5. nahi-to
- Purpose: Define an `else` block for `agar`.
- Usage:
  agar (x > 10) {
      dekho("Badi sankhya!");
  } nahi-to {
      dekho("Choti sankhya!");
  }

---

6. jab-tak
- Purpose: Define a `while` loop.
- Usage:
  jab-tak (x < 10) {
      dekho(x);
      x = x + 1;
  }

---

7. wapas
- Purpose: Return a value from a function.
- Usage:
  kaam add(purna x, purna y) {
      wapas x + y;
  }

---

8. aur / ya / nahi
- Purpose: Logical operators (`and`, `or`, `not`).
- Usage:
  agar (x > 0 aur y < 10) {
      dekho("Sharthan poora!");
  }
  agar (nahi(x == y)) {
      dekho("Samaan nahi hai.");
  }

---

9. poora / jhootha
- Purpose: Boolean values (`true` / `false`).
- Usage:
  naya result = poora;
  agar (result) {
      dekho("Yeh sach hai!");
  }

---

10. purna / do-tirya / string
- Purpose: Data types (`int`, `float`, `string`).
- Usage:
  naya x = purna 10;
  naya y = do-tirya 3.14;
  naya name = string "Bharat";

---

Adding More Keywords
Feel free to add more keywords as you expand your language. Make sure they are intuitive and fit the fun, Hindi theme of the language.

---

Notes
- Keep your code humorous by choosing meaningful and funny Hindi terms for new features!
- Keywords are case-sensitive. Ensure proper usage in your code.

---
